<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-03-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="838" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d838">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Fava</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-15"><hi rend="italic">March 15,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 566.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: In response to your note of the 5th
                            instant I have the honor to say that no reply has yet been received from
                            the governor of Louisiana to the Department’s letter of January 24 last,
                            inclosing copy of your note of the 15th of the same month.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>